## File selection window
**![](data:image/jpeg;base64,)**

- Create new template

- Create template package

- "Templates for templates": Here are available sample templates that you can use as a base for a new template. All .ITX files stored in the Doxee Content Repository folder "master- templates" are displayed here. The folder can be changed in the .properties file of the Business Designer: master.templates.locations=/master-templates/

- *More Templates*: Display the complete or the short list of sample templates (button is only displayed if there is a large number of sample templates)

- Open an existing template or collection

- Open an existing template or collection directly from the list of recently opened files (single click)

- Switch between list view and preview view The file selection window for opening existing files, the selection is limited to ITX files by default (selection criterion in the lower right corner is "*.itx").

## File selection
The file selection (or file picker) can be opened via the folder icon. All the available templates and files from the repository are displayed here. By default, the selection is limited to ITX files (selection criterion on the bottom right is set to "*.itx"). Select *.* to display all file types.

![](data:image/png;base64,)

> Note

*It may happen that files are displayed in light gray color - this indicates that you lack the access rights to open these files.*

By right-clicking in the file selection window you can upload, download, refresh the page, rename, version and delete files.

## Search files
In the file selection window (folder icon), a full text search is available in the upper area. Enter a search term and start the search with Enter. All results that apply in the selected folder or in a subordinate folder are now displayed.

![](data:image/png;base64,)

If the full text search is not sufficient, you can set up an advanced search on the right side by clicking the filter icon.

![](data:image/jpeg;base64,)

In the first field you can choose from a list of existing resource properties or manually enter a property e.g. "templateID". Select whether the property should apply or "not" apply, select how it must be filtered (Like, Equal, Contain etc.) and the search term. In the lower area you can set whether the search should be *recursive*. If you want to add more restrictions, you can add another condition using the filter icon with the +. The added condition is automatically an "and" condition. By clicking on "and" the value changes to "or". This way you can set as many filters as you want. Click on Search to start the process.

> Note

*Multiple search terms must be separated by a comma (,). Use the asterisk (*) for any string or a question mark (?) to represent single characters.*

## Moving Folders and Exporting files
- Moving of folders in ICR - user can now easily move files between folders or subfolders.

Moving is available via basic mouse drag &amp; drop feature and also via context menu (mouse right click).

- To multiselect more files at once press **CTRL + left mouse click **on selected file **or do it via context menu **"MOVE - Add resource to move selection".

![](data:image/png;base64,)

![](data:image/png;base64,)

> Note

*light blue color indicates which files are selected for MOVE operation. Those files are going to be moved to your target destination (by click on 'Move resources here' in context menu or via drag &amp; drop operation)*

- Exporting of files / folders in a **.zip **format is supported now.

Selected files / folders will be exported to .zip format. User is now allowed to export folders and its nested structures.

- From now on user can move / delete / download / export **multiple files at once**, multiselect in file picker was updated.

![](data:image/png;base64,)

> Note

*user is being prompted before multi export / download or delete operation as shown on image below. Browsers might prompt you to allow multi-files downloading.*

*![](data:image/jpeg;base64,)*

## File editing window
![](data:image/jpeg;base64,)

The Business Designer window is divided into three areas:

- The main area in the middle is the **Editor**, it shows the arrangement of the elements in the document and is also used for editing.

- The **outline **on the left shows the logical structure of the template, i.e. all elements that make up the template including their hierarchy. You can unfold the entire element hierarchy in one step by clicking the ![](data:image/png;base64,) -symbol.

- The right area contains the "Menu": Here you will find all editing options:

3a - The **Palette **contains icons for the different element types - insert new elements by dragging the element icon onto the template.

3b - To define the appearance of elements, such as text formats or image sizes, use the **Styles &amp; Properties **section.

3c - Under **Data **the connection to the data structure (XML data) is established so that the fields are available for the dynamic content elements. Switch to further areas: Use ![](data:image/png;base64,) -to switch to the **Static Page Content**: This view is used to edit page areas that are the same on every page when printed (header, footer, left and right area).

With the icons above and below the template contents you can switch directly to the header or footer.

![](data:image/png;base64,)

Use the ![](data:image/png;base64,) -icon to switch to the **Block View **to display and edit blocks.

Use the ![](data:image/png;base64,) -icon to switch back to the **Editor **to edit the template content.

![](data:image/jpeg;base64,)

5 - left toolbar:

5a - **Designer**: Editing view

5b - **Preview**: create a preview from the template and the connected test data (PDF,HTML etc.)

5c - Layout: area for creating **page masters**

5d - Area for creating [Formats and style sheets](/doxee-platform/docs/6-6-business-designer-user-guide-formats-and-style-sheets).

5e - **Variables **for defining global variables (see [Variable / Global Variable](/doxee-platform/docs/dynamic-content#variable-global-variable))

5f - **Test Data Management **for the definition of test cases (see [Data connection  test cases, data inputs](https://docs.doxee.com/docs/6-6-business-designer-user-guide-data-connection-test-cases-data-inputs))

5g - **Other **select from [Decimal formats](/doxee-platform/docs/6-6-business-designer-user-guide-decimal-formats), [Meta Data](http://docs.doxee.com/docs/6-6-business-designer-user-guide-meta-data), [External Resource Management](/doxee-platform/docs/6-6-business-designer-user-guide-create-and-edit-templates-short-instruction-guide#external-resource-management) and [Numbering](/doxee-platform/docs/6-6-business-designer-user-guide-numbering). 

> Note

*Depending on the users role, individual icons and elements may be grayed out.*

## File management options
Various file management options are available on the title bar of the Business Designer:

![](data:image/jpeg;base64,)

![](data:image/png;base64,)

- Close the file

- By clicking on the respective file name you can switch between the currently opened files

- Save as

- Create new template

- Close all the currently opened files

- Show/Hide the verification window (on top of the palette)

- Save file

- Save all the currently opened files

- Editor Settings

- Version information

- User information and sign out

## Editor settings
**![](data:image/jpeg;base64,)**

- Show/Hide: Left Panel (template outline), Right Panel (Palette, Styles &amp; Properties and Data)

- Activate/Deactivate the Floating Toolbar

- Skip block: You can use the arrow keys of the keyboard to switch between elements in the outline and in the editor (horizontal navigation). If this option is enabled, block elements are omitted, i.e. the selection jumps to the next content element.

- Comments: Show/Hide comments (see [Comments](/doxee-platform/docs/6-6-business-designer-user-guide-comments)).

- Restricted Elements  Show/Hide restricted elements and options

## Zoom
The editor (middle area) can be displayed larger. To do so, activate the "undocked toolbar" under "Editor Settings" (see above). Zooming options are available on this toolbar.
